  "prompt": "International Tech companies currently hiring Indian Graduates (Developers)?",
  "response": "As of my last update in October 2023, many international tech companies were actively hiring Indian graduates for developer positions. While specific job openings may vary, here are some companies that are known for recruiting talent from India:\n\n1. **Google** - Known for hiring software engineers and developers in various roles, particularly in areas like cloud computing, Android development, and AI.\n\n2. **Microsoft** - They often have multiple openings in software development, especially related to Azure and other products.\n\n3. **Amazon** - Amazon Web Services (AWS) and their e-commerce platform frequently seek developers for numerous roles.\n\n4. **Facebook (Meta)** - Known for hiring developers for social media technology, AI, and virtual reality.\n\n5. **IBM** - Regularly hires graduates for positions in software development, cloud computing, and data science.\n\n6. **Infosys** - While primarily an Indian company, Infosys has a large international presence and also hires globally.\n\n7. **TCS (Tata Consultancy Services)** - Similar to Infosys, TCS has a strong global reach and hires tech talent for various projects.\n\n8. **Salesforce** - Known for hiring developers particularly focused on cloud solutions and enterprise software.\n\n9. **NVIDIA** - Engages in hiring software developers, especially those with experience in graphics processing and AI.\n\n10. **Accenture** - Regularly seeks tech talent for a variety of projects, often blending technology with consulting.\n\n11. **Adobe** - Offers opportunities in software development, particularly for products related to design and marketing.\n\n12. **SAP** - Frequently hiring for roles related to enterprise software development.\n\n13. **Stripe** - Fintech companies like Stripe often look for developers proficient in payment solutions.\n\n14. **Uber** - Frequently hires developers for their platform, focusing on everything from the app development to backend services.\n\n15. **Zoom** - With the rise of remote work, they have been expanding their engineering teams.\n\nFor the most accurate and current information regarding job openings, it's best to check the careers pages of these companies, LinkedIn, and job portals tailored for tech hires in India. Networking through platforms like LinkedIn or industry-specific meetups can also provide additional insights and opportunities.",
